{
    "name": "Marauder (Raider)",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Tactics",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Base Statistics</b> When not raging, the raider has <b>AC </b>17, touch 13, flat-footed 14; <b>hp </b>55; <b>Fort </b>+7, <b>Will </b>+3; <b>Melee </b>mwk spear +10/+5 (1d8+4/\u00d73) or kukri +9/+4 (1d4+3/18\u2013 20); <b>Str </b>17, <b>Con </b>14; <b>CMB </b>+9; Climb +9, Swim +7"
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "html": "Raiders are the children of the raging storm, wild warriors from the wrinkled hills and jagged mountains. They descend from their aeries with moods as foul and war cries as terrifying as the wild weather that drives them, leaping, scaling the heights, diving from cover to cover, and raining death upon their enemies.<br/><br/>Raiders can be used as skirmishers or scouts, or they can represent any sort of bandits or wild men from the hills who strike the outlying bastions of civilization without warning.<br/><br/>Raiders are often found alone but may travel with a monster hunter (CR 7) or in pairs with a viking (CR 9). Six raiders might form a raiding party with a chieftain, or serve as a chieftain\u2019s honor guard (CR 12)."
        }
    ],
